{"title_page": "Sweet (disambiguation)", "text_new": "{{wiktionary|sweet}}\n'''Sweet''' is the basic taste sensation of [[sweetness]], associated with sugars.\n\n'''Sweet''' may also refer to:keema\u2019s waistline \n\n{{TOC right}}\n==Food==\n* [[Candy]], known in British English-speaking countries as sweets\n* Sweet, a British term for [[confectionery]]\n* Sweet, a term for [[dessert]]\n* [[Sweet (wine)]], a sweetness classification\n\n==Places==\n* [[Sweet River]], Jamaica\n* [[Sweet, Idaho]], United States, an unincorporated community\n\n==People==\n* [[Sweet (surname)]]\n* Sweet, the author citation for [[Robert Sweet (botanist)]]\n* \"Sweet\", the artistic name of former ''Warcraft III'' player [[Chun Jung-Hee]] (born 1983)\n* [[Sweet Charles Sherrell]] (born 1943), an American bassist\n\n==Arts, entertainment, and media==\n===Fictional characters===\n* [[Minor characters of Buffy the Vampire Slayer#Sweet|Sweet]], a minor character in the television series ''Buffy the Vampire Slayer''\n* [[List of characters in Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas#Sean \"Sweet\" Johnson|Sean \"Sweet\" Johnson]], a character in the video game ''Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas''\n* [[List of Touhou Project characters#TH 15 - Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom#Doremy Sweet|Doremy Sweet]], a character in the video game ''Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom''\n\n===Music===\n* [[Sweet (Chara album)|''Sweet'' (Chara album)]], a 1991 album by Chara\n* [[Sweet (Ken Mellons album)|''Sweet'' (Ken Mellons album)]], a 2004 album by Ken Mellons\n* \"Sweet\", a song by Annie from ''[[Don't Stop (Annie album)|Don't Stop]]''\n* \"Sweet\", a song by Common from ''[[The Dreamer/The Believer]]''\n* [[The Sweet]], the 1970s British glam rock band\n** [[The Sweet (album)|''The Sweet'' (album)]], a 1971 album by the band\n\n===Other arts, entertainment, and media===\n* [[Sweet (film)|''Sweet'' (film)]], a 2000 short film directed by James Pilkington and starring Noel Fielding and Julian Barratt\n\n==Brands and enterprises==\n